<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" >

<Paragraph>
Data validation is a feature of Excel that helps to control the kind of information that is entered in a worksheet. It provides users with the following options: 
</Paragraph>

<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>A list of choices</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Restriction of entries to a specific type or size</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Creation of custom settings</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph>
Essential XlsIO has support for reading and writing data validations. This sample focuses on writing a data validation in an Excel template. 
</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}">Features:</TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>

<List>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph><Bold>Text Validation</Bold></Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Validating input text length based on the given constraints</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Below is an illustration of Text Validation in Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\textvalid.png" Width="408" Height="326"/> 
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph><Bold>Time Validation</Bold></Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This validates user-input time and format based on given constraints.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Below is an illustration of Time Validation  in Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\timevalid.png" Width="408" Height="326" /> 
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph><Bold>Date Validation</Bold></Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This validates user-input date and format based on given constraints. </Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Below is an illustration of Date Validation  in Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\datevalid.png" Width="408" Height="326" /> 
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph><Bold>List Validation</Bold></Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This allows creating a drop-down list with the actual data that has to be selected in the preferred cell. Users can quickly select an item from the list and then move on to the next entry without typing unwanted data.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Below is an illustration of List Validation  in Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\listvalid.png" Width="408" Height="326" /> 
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph><Bold>Number Validation</Bold></Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This allows validating a user-input number.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph>Below is an illustration of Number Validation  in Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
 <Image Source="Images\numvalid.png" Width="408" Height="326"/> 
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph></Paragraph>
